text:
The masked frog, masked rock frog or masked cave frog ("Litoria personata") is a frog from Australia. It lives in the Northern Territory's Arnham Land Escarpment.
This frog lives in forests and grasslands. It hides under boulders and in cracks in rocks.
This frog lays eggs in crevices in rocks and in small pools of water, but scientists do not know much about their eggs.
